  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are various legal frameworks to combat money laundering at both national and international levels:\n\n1. International Frameworks:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- Egmont Group of Financial Intelligence Units\n\n2. National Frameworks:\n- Bank Secrecy Act (USA)\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) regulations\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) requirements\n- Suspicious Transaction Reporting mechanisms\n\n3. Key Compliance Measures:\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Reporting suspicious activities\n- Implementing robust internal controls\n- Maintaining detailed financial records\n\n4. Penalties:\n- Significant financial fines\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Asset seizure\n- Business license revocation\n\n5. Preventive Strategies:\n- Enhanced financial transparency\n- International cooperation\n- Technology-driven detection systems\n- Regular risk assessments\n\nThese frameworks aim to detect, prevent, and prosecute money laundering activities across different sectors and jurisdictions.",
